Vesicular stomatitis, Belize
----------------------------
Information received on 29/12/2011 from Dr Miguel Angel Depaz,
Director of Animal Health, Animal Health Department, Belize
Agricultural Health Authority (BAHA), Belmopan, Belize

Summary
Report type Immediate notification
Start date 07/12/2011
Date of first confirmation of the event 20/12/2011
Report date 29/12/2011
Date submitted to OIE 29/12/2011
Reason for notification Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence 28/10/2011
Manifestation of disease Clinical disease
Causal agent Vesicular stomatitis virus
Serotype New Jersey
Nature of diagnosis Clinical, Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1 (VS11/02/01) Belize Rural, Biscayne, Biscayne, BELIZE
Date of start of the outbreak 07/12/2011
Outbreak status Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit Farm

Species Cattle
Susceptible 138
Cases 6
Deaths 0
Destroyed 0
Slaughtered 0

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection- Unknown or
inconclusive

Epidemiological comments: No animal other than the six cases was
found with clinical signs in the affected farm and other farms in the
affected village.

Control measures- Measures applied

Control of arthropods
Quarantine
Movement control inside the country
Screening
Vaccination prohibited
No treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Laboratorio de Diagn√≥stico de Enfermedades
Vesiculares (LADIVES) (Regional Reference Laboratory)
Tests and results
Species Cattle
Test antigen (Ag) detection ELISA
Test date 20/12/2011
Result Positive

Future Reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.
